<h1>Problem 1796 - 2024 MODS Geometry Contest, P2 of 6, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Let \(\triangle ABC\) have incenter \(I\) and let its incircle \(\omega\) touch \(CA\), \(AB\) at points \(E\), \(F\). Let the nine-point circle of \(\triangle BIC\) meet \(\omega\) at \(T \notin BC\) and let lines \(BI\), \(CI\) meet line \(EF\) at points \(X\), \(Y\).</p>
<p>Prove that an intersection point of circles \(TYE\), \(TXF\) lies on line \(AI\).</p>
